<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#ffffff"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000080"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#ffffff" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Snowielder</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Should AC be sacrificed fo saves?<P>To me, it seems as though sacrificing a few points of AC for an extra 5 or 10 points in any save area is worth it, but I often times see armor with no saves and higher AC sell for more than armor with a save or saves and slightly lower AC.<P>Does class matter in this arguement?  I am a shaman, so I would like to know specifically for shaman, but a general analysis of this arguement would be appreciated also.<P>Snowielder<BR>13th level shaman (well, 12 thanks to that Lake Rathe incident), but soon to be 13 again.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Valka</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well, for general cases, increased resist<BR>scores of 10-20 do not in fact decrease your<BR>chance of resisting a magical attack,at <BR>least not significantly.<P>Of course if you get enough of this<BR>equipment, you can avoid a lot of magical<BR>attacks (once you get into the 100-200<BR>range) Of course you're going to have to<BR>sacrafice a LOT of ac for this, so it's <BR>really only done in specific circumstances<BR>(ie. dragon raids)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tugg Boat</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Not a whole lot of creatures cast on a continual basis, but they all melee quite a bit. I wouldn't give up AC for resists. Especially when shaman can buff EVERY resist via spell.<P>Now if you are on a PVP server, screw AC <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"> Go full resists while PKing, and have a 2nd set of "AC" armor while XPing.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aurelias</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Also npc casters tend to dish out the damage. my wizard still looks forward to the day he can hit for double 40+ and bash as well   <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"><BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Friday</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Have two sets of gear one for resists (used in certain situations only) and one for ac/wis.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gazgaz-53</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Me have 3 sets of armor one for AC one for Wis dome and 3rd for cha  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"> me cha is now 105  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"> me very pritty troll  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"><P>Gazgaz chaman on E Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aktunka</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">These folks are right. In most situations the AC is a better choice, but in certain situations, you must go with the right resists or you accomplish nothing but your own deaths. Nothing pointed this out more to me then a failed Vox run one night. <P>Vox fears and has that damn cold breath thinger spell or whatever it is. There was actually close to 60 folks that kept trying to take her down, and they spent most of thier time running around feared and taking cold damage. After about 8 attempts another guild came in and moved in on her (much to the chagrin of those that had been trying to kill her) and with a total of only 18 people they killed her the first try. Everyone tanked, not many were feared, or at least not for very long when they were, and apparently not much damage was taken, because they didnt lose anyone. <P>When 18 people can take  Vox on the first shot when 60 couldnt take her, that goes to show the difference that the right equipment can make. I have heard that the minimum for magic and cold resist you should have on vox is minimum of 100 each. Anyhow, just a thing to illustrate this. Good luck.<P>Aktunka Wormflinger<BR>lvl 51 Troll Shaman<BR>Mith Marr</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</FONT>
